
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box on Page 03
And	I go to Page 07 of Thoracic MRT
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Clavicular mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I know' radio button

When I select 'Characterization III' tab
Then 'No' radio button is enabled
And 'Little' radio button is enabled
And 'Strong' radio button is enabled


And 'Soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Perifocal sclerosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Surrounding inflammatory reaction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Intraosseous abscess' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration of soft tissues' checkbox is enabled
And 'Infiltration of adjacent bone' checkbox is enabled

And 'Pathologic fracture' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Little' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled
And 'In the nidus' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Strong' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled
And 'In the nidus' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Pathologic fracture' checkbox
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
